:::summary
Parley Parker Pratt (1807–1857) was one of the original Twelve Apostles of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints and one of the most prolific and influential writers, missionaries, and theologians of the early Restoration. His book *Key to the Science of Theology* was the first systematic presentation of Latter-day Saint theology and stands as a landmark of LDS intellectual history.
:::

